---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Oil & Energy — Brent Crude, WTI, LNG Prices | HormuzWatch" description="Live oil prices, energy market analysis, and LNG impact data for the Strait of Hormuz crisis. Brent, WTI, TTF gas, and gasoline price tracking.">
  <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-8">
    <div class="mb-8">
      <nav class="text-sm text-slate-400 mb-4">
        <a href="/" class="hover:text-white">Home</a> <span class="mx-2">›</span> <span class="text-white">Oil & Energy</span>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-2">Oil & Energy Markets</h1>
      <p class="text-slate-400">Live energy prices and market analysis during the Strait of Hormuz crisis</p>
    </div>

    <div id="oil-data-container">
      <!-- Price Cards -->
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-4 mb-8">
        <div class="bg-slate-900 border border-slate-800 rounded-xl p-6">
          <div class="text-xs text-slate-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">Brent Crude</div>
          <div class="text-3xl font-bold text-white" id="brent-price">--</div>
          <div class="text-sm mt-1" id="brent-change">--</div>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-slate-900 border border-slate-800 rounded-xl p-6">
          <div class="text-xs text-slate-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">WTI Crude</div>
          <div class="text-3xl font-bold text-white" id="wti-price">--</div>
          <div class="text-sm text-slate-400 mt-1">Pre-crisis baseline: $65.00</div>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-slate-900 border border-slate-800 rounded-xl p-6">
          <div class="text-xs text-slate-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">EU Gas (TTF)</div>
          <div class="text-3xl font-bold text-white" id="ttf-price">--</div>
          <div class="text-sm text-slate-400 mt-1">Pre-crisis baseline: $30.00</div>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-slate-900 border border-slate-800 rounded-xl p-6">
          <div class="text-xs text-slate-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">US Gasoline</div>
          <div class="text-3xl font-bold text-white" id="gas-price">--</div>
          <div class="text-sm text-slate-400 mt-1">Pre-crisis baseline: $2.97/gal</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Oil Price Chart -->
      <div class="bg-slate-900 border border-slate-800 rounded-xl p-6 mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">Brent Crude — Price Trend</h2>
        <canvas id="oil-chart" width="800" height="300" class="w-full"></canvas>
      </div>

      <!-- Oil Explained -->
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-8">
        <div class="bg-slate-900 border border-slate-800 rounded-xl p-6">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">Why the Strait of Hormuz Matters for Oil</h2>
          <div class="space-y-4 text-sm text-slate-300">
            <p>The Strait of Hormuz is the world's most critical oil chokepoint. Approximately 20-21% of the world's daily oil supply transits through this narrow waterway, equivalent to roughly 17-18 million barrels per day. This includes crude oil, condensates, and refined petroleum products from Saudi Arabia, Iraq, Kuwait, UAE, Iran, and Qatar.</p>
            <p>When the strait is disrupted, the impact on global oil prices is immediate and severe. The current crisis has seen Brent crude surge from a pre-crisis level of around $72 per barrel to over $116 per barrel — a more than 60% increase that cascades through every sector of the global economy.</p>
            <p>Unlike many other commodities, oil supply cannot be quickly rerouted. While pipelines like the East-West Pipeline across Saudi Arabia and the UAE's ADCOP can bypass the strait, their combined capacity is only a fraction of the strait's normal throughput. The Cape of Good Hope adds 16-22 days to voyages, dramatically increasing shipping costs and insurance premiums.</p>
            <p>The Strategic Petroleum Reserve (SPR) provides a temporary buffer — currently estimated at about 28 days of coverage — but this is a finite resource that cannot substitute for normal flow indefinitely.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="bg-slate-900 border border-slate-800 rounded-xl p-6">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">LNG & Natural Gas Impact</h2>
          <div class="space-y-4 text-sm text-slate-300">
            <p>Approximately 25% of the world's liquefied natural gas (LNG) trade passes through the Strait of Hormuz, primarily from Qatar — the world's second-largest LNG exporter. Qatar's Ras Laffan Industrial City, home to its largest LNG export facility, lost approximately 17% of its capacity from Iranian drone and missile strikes in late February and early March 2026.</p>
            <p>The LNG disruption has had a disproportionate impact on Asian importers. Japan, which relies on LNG for a significant portion of its electricity generation, and South Korea, a major LNG consumer, face the most acute shortages. North American LNG producers have gained market share as a substitute, but capacity constraints limit how quickly this supply can scale.</p>
            <p>European gas prices (TTF) have also been affected, though less severely than during the 2022 energy crisis, as Europe has diversified its supply sources significantly since the Russia-Ukraine conflict began. However, the combined effect of reduced LNG availability and higher oil prices has pushed TTF above pre-crisis levels.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Tanker Rates -->
      <div class="bg-slate-900 border border-slate-800 rounded-xl p-6 mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">Tanker Freight Rates</h2>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
          <div class="p-4 bg-slate-800/50 rounded-lg">
            <div class="text-xs text-slate-400 mb-1">Current Rate (AG-East TD3C)</div>
            <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-red-400" id="tanker-rate">240 WS</div>
          </div>
          <div class="p-4 bg-slate-800/50 rounded-lg">
            <div class="text-xs text-slate-400 mb-1">Pre-Crisis Rate</div>
            <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-300">50 WS</div>
          </div>
          <div class="p-4 bg-slate-800/50 rounded-lg">
            <div class="text-xs text-slate-400 mb-1">Change</div>
            <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-red-400">+380%</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>

<script>
  async function loadOilData() {
    try {
      const [dashRes, oilRes] = await Promise.all([
        fetch('/api/dashboard'),
        fetch('/api/oil')
      ]);
      const dashJson = await dashRes.json();
      const oilJson = await oilRes.json();
      
      if (dashJson.success) {
        const d = dashJson.data;
        const brentEl = document.getElementById('brent-price');
        const brentCh = document.getElementById('brent-change');
        if (brentEl) brentEl.textContent = '$' + (d.oilPrice?.brentPrice?.toFixed(2) || '--');
        if (brentCh) {
          const pct = d.oilPrice?.changePercent24h || 0;
          brentCh.textContent = `${pct > 0 ? '+' : ''}${pct.toFixed(2)}%`;
          brentCh.className = `text-sm mt-1 ${pct > 0 ? 'text-red-400' : 'text-green-400'}`;
        }
      }
      
      if (oilJson) {
        const wtiEl = document.getElementById('wti-price');
        const ttfEl = document.getElementById('ttf-price');
        const gasEl = document.getElementById('gas-price');
        if (wtiEl && oilJson.wti) wtiEl.textContent = '$' + oilJson.wti.toFixed(2);
        if (ttfEl && oilJson.ttf) ttfEl.textContent = '€' + oilJson.ttf.toFixed(2);
        if (gasEl && oilJson.gasoline) gasEl.textContent = '$' + oilJson.gasoline.toFixed(2) + '/gal';
      }
      
      // Draw oil chart
      const canvas = document.getElementById('oil-chart') as HTMLCanvasElement;
      if (canvas && dashJson.success) {
        const sparkline = dashJson.data.oilPrice?.sparkline || [];
        if (sparkline.length > 0) {
          const ctx = canvas.getContext('2d');
          if (!ctx) return;
          const w = canvas.width;
          const h = canvas.height;
          const padding = 30;
          
          ctx.clearRect(0, 0, w, h);
          
          const min = Math.min(...sparkline) - 5;
          const max = Math.max(...sparkline) + 5;
          const range = max - min;
          const stepX = (w - padding * 2) / (sparkline.length - 1);
          
          // Grid lines
          ctx.strokeStyle = '#1e293b';
          ctx.lineWidth = 1;
          for (let i = 0; i <= 4; i++) {
            const y = padding + (i / 4) * (h - padding * 2);
            ctx.beginPath();
            ctx.moveTo(padding, y);
            ctx.lineTo(w - padding, y);
            ctx.stroke();
            
            const val = max - (i / 4) * range;
            ctx.fillStyle = '#64748b';
            ctx.font = '10px Inter';
            ctx.fillText('$' + val.toFixed(0), 0, y + 3);
          }
          
          // Gradient fill
          const gradient = ctx.createLinearGradient(0, 0, 0, h);
          gradient.addColorStop(0, 'rgba(239, 68, 68, 0.2)');
          gradient.addColorStop(1, 'rgba(239, 68, 68, 0.02)');
          
          ctx.beginPath();
          ctx.moveTo(padding, h - padding);
          for (let i = 0; i < sparkline.length; i++) {
            const x = padding + i * stepX;
            const y = h - padding - ((sparkline[i] - min) / range) * (h - padding * 2);
            ctx.lineTo(x, y);
          }
          ctx.lineTo(padding + (sparkline.length - 1) * stepX, h - padding);
          ctx.closePath();
          ctx.fillStyle = gradient;
          ctx.fill();
          
          // Line
          ctx.beginPath();
          for (let i = 0; i < sparkline.length; i++) {
            const x = padding + i * stepX;
            const y = h - padding - ((sparkline[i] - min) / range) * (h - padding * 2);
            if (i === 0) ctx.moveTo(x, y);
            else ctx.lineTo(x, y);
          }
          ctx.strokeStyle = '#ef4444';
          ctx.lineWidth = 2;
          ctx.stroke();
          
          // Last point
          const lastX = padding + (sparkline.length - 1) * stepX;
          const lastY = h - padding - ((sparkline[sparkline.length - 1] - min) / range) * (h - padding * 2);
          ctx.beginPath();
          ctx.arc(lastX, lastY, 4, 0, Math.PI * 2);
          ctx.fillStyle = '#ef4444';
          ctx.fill();
          ctx.strokeStyle = '#0f172a';
          ctx.lineWidth = 2;
          ctx.stroke();
        }
      }
    } catch(e) {
      console.error('Failed to load oil data:', e);
    }
  }
  loadOilData();
  setInterval(loadOilData, 60000);
</script>
